section.div: CADET is a research-grade toolkit for transformer-centric automated essay scoring. The repository operationalises prompt-aware data pipelines, neural regressors, and reproducible evaluation routines targeting the ASAP benchmark and related educational assessment corpora.

Aurora Sight-to-Sound is a research pipeline that converts images or videos into musically coherent compositions by mapping visual features—semantic, color, and texture—to interpretable musical attributes, generating symbolic scores, and synthesizing expressive audio, with traceable explanations at each step.

Resume Insight Engine is a modular framework for parsing resumes, engineering features, scoring candidate fit, and surfacing explainable insights. The toolkit stitches together NLP-driven parsers, transformer-based scoring models, and ranking utilities so talent teams can compare candidates and draft actionable feedback with minimal effort.

Adaptive Guided Query Retrieval (AGQ-IR) is a conversational information retrieval engine that fuses semantic embeddings with structured product attributes. The system iteratively refines search focus via user feedback, dynamically adjusts learning rates, and can probe semantic clusters using density-based questions (HDBSCAN) for richer guidance.
AI Text Detection using BiLSTM — A deep learning model to classify whether a piece of text is AI-generated or human-written.

This project is a machine learning application that predicts the score of an essay based on its content. It utilizes a Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) neural network along with Word2Vec embeddings for text processing.

ImageEnhancementAutoencoder: A repository containing code for an image enhancement autoencoder using TensorFlow and Keras. Enhance low-resolution images with perceptual loss for improved visual quality.

Ready-to-run cloud templates for RAG, AI pipelines, and enterprise search with live data. 🐳Docker-friendly.⚡Always in sync with Sharepoint, Google Drive, S3, Kafka, PostgreSQL, real-time data APIs, and more.
